3. 

In these Regulations – 

“Act of 2014” means the Health Identifiers Act 2014 (No. 15 of 2014); 

“care” includes examination, investigation and diagnosis; 

“Data Protection Regulation” means Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the 
European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 20161 on the protection of 
natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free 
movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC (General Data 
Protection Regulation); 

“health data” means personal data relating to physical or mental health; 

“health practitioner” has the same meaning as it has in section 2 of the Act of 
2014; 

“health services provider” has the same meaning as it has in section 2 of the 
Act of 2014.
